node.title: Louisiana Judge Pressed to Resign After Racist Language Heard in Video Filmed at Home
node.description: The video recorded in Michelle Odinet's home shows a TV with security footage of an attempted burglary playing while racist comments are made by those watching.

node.title: Warner fit to play in Adelaide, Richardson locked in for Ashes berth
node.description: A rib injury will not keep David Warner from playing the second Ashes Test in Adelaide, while Jhye Richardson is confirmed to replace Josh Hazlewood in the bowling attack.

node.title: Quarantine halved for fully vaccinated close contacts of Omicron cases in Canberra

node.title: Vaccines alone won't stop Omicron. So which COVID measures are in place in your state?
node.description: The World Health Organization says vaccines alone "will not get any country out of this crisis" as Omicron spreads at an unprecedented rate. So what do they recommend will help? And what are the rules in your state?

node.title: Police arrest three people after death of man dropped at Takanini medical centre

node.title: James Webb Space Telescope launch delayed
node.description: The launch of the $10 billion successor to Hubble is slipping at least two days due to a last-minute data relay issue.
